could detect the CIB distortion at $\\approx 5\\sigma$ significance,\neven after marginalizing over foregrounds. A measurement of this signal would\nprovide new information on the star formation history of the Universe, and the\ndistortion anisotropies may be accessible by near-future ground-based\nexperiments.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 4 Feb 2022 18:03:04 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 26 Apr 2022 01:16:31 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Thu, 28 Jul 2022 17:19:55 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-07-29"}
